{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/adapters/fs.rs:2993-3023` still does not use `started_at` when it falls back from a supplied `run_id` to a single open runless row. As written, any named completion with the right bead/project will finalize that row even if the caller's `started_at` points at a different attempt. That violates the service contract in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:466-469` and can backfill the wrong legacy attempt. Require `entries[*index].started_at == started_at` before accepting the runless fallback, and add a regression test that a mismatched timestamp is rejected.","rationale":"The accepted fix explicitly called out using `started_at` to disambiguate. The current implementation accepts the fallback unconditionally, so bad or stale caller metadata can still finalize the wrong run."},{"body":"`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:429-441` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:564-576` now replace every omitted `plan_hash` with `snapshot.plan_hash` before the lineage layer matches an existing row. Because `persist_plan` can later advance `snapshot.plan_hash` (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:347-385`), an idempotent start/completion replay against a row that already carries the older plan hash will now trip the conflict checks in `src/adapters/fs.rs:2711-2725` or `src/adapters/fs.rs:3159-3201`. The fallback needs to happen only when the matched row lacks `plan_hash`, not blindly at the service boundary; please add replay coverage across a later plan update.","rationale":"This change regresses replay/repair semantics: once the milestone snapshot moves to a new plan version, retrying the same start or completion with `plan_hash: None` can fail even though the stored lineage row is otherwise the correct target."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone lineage changes and found two correctness gaps. The new journal-detail sync tests look reasonable, but the runless-to-named completion path still ignores `started_at`, and the service-level `plan_hash` fallback can break idempotent replays after a later `persist_plan` updates the snapshot hash."}